<!-- Egypt Travel Notes -->
<section id="travel-notes" class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 pt-6 pb-4">

  <details class="bg-neutral-100 rounded-2xl p-6 shadow-sm">

    <summary class="text-2xl font-bold cursor-pointer flex items-center justify-between">
      Travel Notes
      <span class="text-sm opacity-60">▼</span>
    </summary>

    <p class="text-sm opacity-80 leading-relaxed mt-4 mb-5">
      We’ve visited Egypt three times between 2023 and 2025. Each trip revealed something different, not just in the places themselves, but in how they’re experienced.
    </p>

    <div class="space-y-5 text-sm opacity-80 leading-relaxed">

      <div>
        <p class="font-semibold mb-1">Before we went</p>
        <p>
          We arrived with concerns about safety and food, even packing muesli bars to keep things simple. In hindsight, much of that came from uncertainty rather than reality.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <p class="font-semibold mb-1">What made the biggest difference</p>
        <p>
          Having a local team in place changed everything. With logistics taken care of, we were free to focus on the experience itself.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <p class="font-semibold mb-1">What surprised us most</p>
        <p>
          Despite early expectations, we always felt safe. Encounters with locals could be persistent at times, but never threatening. Over time, we came to understand these interactions as part of the local economy, direct, but human.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <p class="font-semibold mb-1">What changed over three visits</p>
        <p>
          Our first trip was fast paced, moving quickly between major sites. By the second and third visits, we slowed everything down, allowing time to explore, reflect, and film. That shift changed the experience completely.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <p class="font-semibold mb-1">What we’d do differently next time</p>
        <p>
          We understand tipping very differently now. It’s a meaningful part of everyday life for many people we met. Next time, we’d come better prepared so those small interactions feel natural, not hesitant.
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>

  </details>

</section>
